    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"2-77\"><h2>2-77</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Multiple Representations of Linear Functions</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Practices linear modeling and multiple representations with slope, points, equations, graphs, and tables.</div>\n<p><strong>USING A TABLE</strong></p>\n<p>Use the information in problem 2-75 to answer these questions.</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li>Now approach this problem using a table. Make a table with two columns, the first labeled “Days Since Birth” and the second labeled “Weight in Grams.” In the first column, write the numbers $0$ through $10$.</li>\n<li>Use Colleen’s measurements to fill one entry in the table.</li>\n<li>Use the chick’s growth rate to complete the table.</li>\n<li>According to your table, how much did the chick weigh the day it was hatched? When will the chick weigh $140$ grams? Do these answers match your answers from the graph? Which method do you think is more accurate? Why?</li>\n</ol>\n<table class=\"response-table small-table\">\n<tr><th>Days Since Birth</th><th>Weight in Grams</th></tr>\n<tr><td>$0$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$1$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$2$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$3$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$4$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$5$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$6$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$7$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$8$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$9$</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>$10$</td><td></td></tr>\n</table>\n</section>",
