    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"4-8\"><h2>4-8</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Creates a scatterplot, draws a line of best fit, and uses it to make a prediction.</div>\n<p>Smallville High School Principal is concerned about his school’s Advanced Placement (AP) test scores. He wonders if there is a relationship between the students’ performance in class and their AP test scores so he randomly selects a sample of ten students who took AP examinations and compares their final exam scores to their AP test scores. <a class=\"etool-link\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/omn9rbq6da\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">4-8 HW eTool</a></p>\n<table class=\"response-table small-table\">\n<tr><th>AP Score</th><td>5</td><td>1</td><td>4</td><td>2</td><td>1</td><td>4</td><td>2</td><td>1</td><td>3</td><td>5</td></tr>\n<tr><th>Final Score (%)</th><td>97</td><td>70</td><td>84</td><td>66</td><td>62</td><td>79</td><td>73</td><td>63</td><td>82</td><td>90</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p>Create a scatterplot on graph paper. Draw a line of best fit that represents the data. Use the equation of your line of best fit to predict the final exam score of another Smallville HS student who scored a $3$ on their AP test.</p>\n<div class=\"grid-workspace\"></div>\n</section>",
