    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"Describing-Association\"><h2>Describing Association</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Summarizes form, direction, strength, and outliers when describing association in scatterplots.</div>\n<p>An association, or relationship, between two numerical variables can be described by its <strong>form</strong>, <strong>direction</strong>, <strong>strength</strong>, and <strong>outliers</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <strong>form</strong> of an association describes the shape of the pattern: linear, non-linear, or clusters.</li>\n<li>The <strong>direction</strong> is positive if one variable increases as the other increases, negative if one variable increases as the other decreases, and no association if there is no apparent pattern.</li>\n<li>The <strong>strength</strong> describes how much scatter there is in the data away from a line of best fit.</li>\n<li>An <strong>outlier</strong> is a data value that does not seem to fit the overall pattern.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>",
