    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"5-61\"><h2>5-61</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Models prize money increasing by a constant amount for each incorrect caller.</div>\n<div><div><div><p>Your favorite radio station, WCPM, is having a contest. The DJ poses a question to the listeners. If the caller answers correctly, he or she wins the prize money. If the caller answers incorrectly, $\\$20$ is added to the prize money and the next caller is eligible to win. The current question is difficult, and no one has won for two days.</p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Lucky you! Fourteen people already called in today with incorrect answers, so when you called (with the right answer, of course) you won $\\$735$! How much was the prize worth at the beginning of the day today?</p></li><li><p>Suppose the contest always starts with $\\$100$. How many people would have to guess incorrectly for the winner to get $\\$1360$?</p></li></ol></div></div></div>\n</section>",
