    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-13\">\n<h2>6-13</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Uses residual information and extrapolation reasoning to interpret a model and its slope/intercept in context.</div>\n<div><p> The warehouse store wants to offer a super-sized $600 \\text{ in}^{2}$<sup> </sup>box. \t</p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>The residual for this box is $1005$ grams. What is the actual weight of a $600 \\text{ in}^{2}$ box?   </p></li><li><p>Why do you suppose the residual is so large?  </p></li><li><p>Interpret the meaning of the slope and <em>$y$</em>-intercept of your model in the context of this problem. Does the <em>$y$</em>-intercept make sense in the context of the problem?  </p></li></ol></div>\n</section>",
