    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-22\">\n<h2>6-22</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Uses bivariate data collection and linear modeling to predict height from forearm length in context.</div>\n<div><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-sm-8\"><p>In 1997, an anthropologist discovered an early humanoid in Europe. As part of the analysis of the specimen, the anthropologist needed to determine the approximate height of the individual. The skeletal remains were highly limited, with only an ulna bone (forearm) being complete. The bone measured $26.4$ cm in length. </p><p><strong>Your Task: </strong>Consider how you could determine how tall the humanoid was. Discuss the questions below with your team. Be ready to share your responses with the rest of the class. </p></div></div></div>\n</section>",
