    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-42\">\n<h2>6-42</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Creates a scatterplot and LSRL from data, writes the model, computes residuals, and sums squared residuals.</div>\n<div><p>Robbie’s class collected the following view tube data in problem 6-1. </p><table><tbody><tr><th><p> Distance from the Wall (in) </p></th><th><p> Width of field of view (in) </p></th></tr><tr><td><p>$144$</p></td><td><p>$20.7$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$132$</p></td><td><p>19.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$120$</p></td><td><p>17.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$96$</p></td><td><p>14.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$84$</p></td><td><p>13.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$72$</p></td><td><p>11.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>$60$</p></td><td><p>9.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>checksum $708$</em></p></td><td><p><em>checksum 106.2</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Use your calculator to make a scatterplot and graph the least squares regression line (LSRL). Sketch the graph and LSRL on your paper. Remember to put a scale on the <em>x</em>-axis and <em>y</em>-axis of your sketch. Write the equation of the LSRL rounded to four decimal places.</p></li><li><p>With your calculator, find the residuals as you did in part (c) of problem 6-33. Make a table with the <em>distance from wall (inches) </em>as the first column, and <em>residual (inches)</em> in the second column. What is the sum of the squares of the residuals?</p></li></ol></div>\n</section>",
