    "html": "<section class=\"problem math-note\" id=\"notes\">\n<h2>Math Notes: Residuals</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Math Notes</span> Lesson 6.1.4</div>\n<div>\n<p>We measure how far a prediction made by our model is from the actual observed value with a residual:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">$\\text{residual}=\\text{actual}-\\text{predicted}$</p>\n<p>A residual has the same units as the $y$-axis. A residual can be graphed with a vertical segment that extends from the point to the line or curve made by the best-fit model. The length of this segment, in the units of the $y$-axis, is the residual. A positive residual means that the actual value is greater than the predicted value; a negative residual means that the actual value is less than the predicted value.</p>\n</div>\n</section>",
