    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-47\">\n<h2>6-47</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Creates a scatterplot and LSRL from data, then analyzes how an outlier changes the linear model and predictions.</div>\n<div><p> In problem 6-1, you completed an investigation that helped Robbie use a viewing tube to see a football game. Typical data is shown in the table below. </p><table><tbody><tr><th><p>Distance from wall (in)</p></th><th><p>Width of field of view (in)</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>144</p></td><td><p>20.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>132</p></td><td><p>19.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>120</p></td><td><p>17.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>108</p></td><td><p>16.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>96</p></td><td><p>14.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>84</p></td><td><p>13.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>72</p></td><td><p>11.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>9.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>checksum 816</em></p></td><td><p><em>checksum 122.4</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Use your calculator or <a class=\"etool-link\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/ymp5jpfqfu\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">6-47 Student eTool</a> to create a scatterplot and LSRL. Sketch the graph on your paper. What is the equation of the LSRL? Click in the lower right corner of the graph to view it in full-screen mode.   \t\t</p></li><li><p>When entering the data in her calculator, Amy accidentally entered (144, 10.7) for the first data point. Make this change to your data and sketch the new point and new LSRL in a different color. Would you consider this point an outlier? </p></li><li><p>What is the impact of the outlier? Will Amy’s predictions for the field of view be too large or too small? How do you know?  </p></li></ol></div>\n<div class=\"captured-figures\"><figure><img alt=\"Captured figure for 6-47\" class=\"figure-img\" src=\"assets/6-47.png\"/><figcaption>Captured figure for 6-47</figcaption></figure></div>\n</section>",
