    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-73\">\n<h2>6-73</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Analyzes pencil data with LSRL, residual plot, prediction, and residual interpretation.</div>\n<div><p>Sam collected data in problem 6-4 by measuring the pencils of her classmates. She recorded the length of the painted part of each pencil and its weight. Her data is listed in the table below. </p><table><tbody><tr><th><p> Length (cm)</p></th><td><p>$13.7$</p></td><td><p>$12.6$</p></td><td><p>$10.7$</p></td><td><p> $9.8$</p></td><td><p> $9.3$</p></td><td><p> $8.5$</p></td><td><p> $7.2$</p></td><td><p> $6.3$</p></td><td><p> $5.2$</p></td><td><p> $4.5$</p></td><td><p> $3.8$ </p></td></tr><tr><th><p> Weight (g)</p></th><td><p> $4.7$</p></td><td><p> $4.3$</p></td><td><p> $4.1$</p></td><td><p> $3.8$</p></td><td><p> $3.6$</p></td><td><p>$3.4$</p></td><td><p> $3.0$</p></td><td><p> $2.8$</p></td><td><p> $2.7$</p></td><td><p>$2.3$</p></td><td><p> $2.3$</p></td></tr></tbody></table><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Graph the data on your calculator and sketch the graph on your paper.</p></li><li><p>What is the equation of the LSRL? Sketch it on your scatterplot.</p></li><li><p>Create a residual plot and sketch it on your paper.</p></li><li><p>Interpret your residual plot. Does it seem appropriate to use a linear model to make predictions about the weight of a pencil?</p></li><li><p>The teacher’s pencil, when it was new, had a painted part 16.8 cm long and weighed 6 g. What was the residual? Consider the precision of the original data and use an appropriate number of decimal places.</p></li><li><p>What does a positive residual mean in this context?</p></li></ol></div>\n</section>",
