    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-84\">\n<h2>6-84</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Creates original headlines that intentionally confuse association with causation.</div>\n<div><p>Come up with your own original news headlines. The first sentence should contain a reasonable link between two variables. The second statement should be a clear misinterpretation of the link.  Two examples are given below.</p><p>1<sup>st</sup>  Statement: Facial Tissue Linked to Colds and Flu. <br/> \t2<sup>nd</sup> Statement: Surgeon General Calls for a Shift to Paper Towels!  </p><p>1<sup>st</sup>  Statement: Bathing Suits Tied to Sunburn. <br/> \t2<sup>nd</sup> Statement: Doctors Recommend: Swim Naked! </p></div>\n</section>",
