    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-92\">\n<h2>6-92</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Interprets a perfect linear correlation and explains what it means for variability and prediction.</div>\n<div><div><p class=\"\">Suppose Alyse collected the following data for five random students in her class: Explore using the <a class=\"etool-link\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/pt2fjwf8la\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">6-92 Student eTool</a>. Click in the lower right corner of the graph to view it in full-screen mode.</p><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-sm-6\"><img alt=\"Figure for 6-92\" class=\"figure-img\" src=\"assets/6-92.png\"/></div><div class=\"col-sm-6\"><table><tbody><tr><th><p class=\"\">Shoe size</p></th><th><p class=\"\">Height (cm)</p></th></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$6$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$154$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$7\\frac{1}{2}$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$160$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$8$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$162$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$8\\frac{1}{2}$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$164$</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=\"\">$10$</p></td><td><p class=\"\">$170$</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p class=\"\">What is the correlation coefficient? Why is the data unusual? In the context of this problem, what does the correlation coefficient tell Alyse about the association between height and shoe size for these very unusual students? </p></li><li><p class=\"\">What can Alyse say about the variability in height in her unusual class? What can she say about predicting height for a student?  </p></li></ol></div></div>\n</section>",
