    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"6-100\">\n<h2>6-100</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Identifies plausible lurking variables behind observational-study headlines.</div>\n<div><div><p class=\"\">Here are some more news headlines from real observational studies. Just as you did in problem 6-83, determine at least one plausible lurking variable that could explain the cause and effect. Remember, do not argue about the link expressed in the headline. Accept the association or link as true. Your task is to find the other variable(s) that could be the actual cause(s).</p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\"><li><p class=\"\">“Teens with own cars more likely to crash”</p></li><li><p class=\"\">“Bottled water linked to healthier babies”</p></li></ol></div></div>\n</section>",
