    "html": "<section class=\"problem math-note\" id=\"math-note-nonlinear-models\">\n<h2>Math Note: Non-Linear Models</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Methods and Meanings</span> Curved Best-Fit Models</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Summarizes when non-linear models are useful and lists common model forms.</div>\n<p>Sometimes a non-linear model best fits the data, and therefore makes better predictions, than a linear model. This is usually made apparent by comparing the residual plots of various models.</p>\n<p>A good model should also be representative of the physical situation. Exponential models can make sense for decay over time, quadratic models can make sense for relationships involving area or projectile height, and power models can make sense when one measurement depends on a power of another.</p>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div><p>Linear: $y=mx+b$</p></div>\n<div><p>Exponential: $y=ab^x$</p></div>\n<div><p>Power: $y=ax^b$</p></div>\n<div><p>Quadratic: $y=ax^2+bx+c$</p></div>\n</div>\n</section>",
    "assets": [],
    "resources": [],
