    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"10-8\">\n<h2>10-8</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Other: Statistics and Probability / Two-Way Tables and Association</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Converts percent survey data into a two-way table and uses it to reason about association.</div>\n<div>\n<p>In a recent survey of college freshmen, $35\\%$ of students checked the box next to “Exercise regularly,” $33\\%$ checked the box next to “Eat five or more servings of fruits and vegetables a day,” and $57\\%$ checked the box next to “Neither.”</p>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\">\n<li>Draw a two-way table to represent this situation.</li>\n<li>What is the probability that a freshman who was surveyed exercises regularly <em>and</em> eats 5 servings of fruits and vegetables each day?</li>\n<li>What is the probability that a freshman who was surveyed exercises regularly <em>or</em> eats 5 servings of fruits and vegetables each day?</li>\n<li>Is there an association between eating fruits and vegetables and exercise? Create a conditional relative frequency table to help answer this question.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</section>",
