    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"10-59\">\n<h2>10-59</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Other: Statistics and Probability / Two-Way Tables and Association</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Uses a two-way table to calculate percentages, conditional probabilities, and assess association between categorical variables.</div>\n<p>Delenn is re-examining the difference in backpacks among different grade levels at her school. (She previously collected data in Lesson 8.1.3.) Now she has collected a new random sample of $100$ students to see if there are categorical relationships between carrying backpacks and graduating classes.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th></th><th>Freshmen</th><th>Sophomore</th><th>Junior</th><th>Senior</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><th>Backpack</th><td>8</td><td>16</td><td>18</td><td>19</td></tr>\n<tr><th>No Backpack</th><td>3</td><td>6</td><td>14</td><td>16</td></tr>\n<tr><th>Total</th><td>11</td><td>22</td><td>32</td><td>35</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\">\n<li>Based on her sample, what percentage of students do not carry a backpack at school?</li>\n<li>If a junior is chosen, what is the probability they are carrying a backpack?</li>\n<li>If a student is not carrying a backpack, what is the probability they are a junior or senior?</li>\n<li>Is there a relationship between graduating class and carrying a backpack at school? Show your evidence.</li>\n</ol>\n</section>",
