    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"10-113\">\n<h2>10-113</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Other: Statistics and Probability</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Interprets association in a two-way frequency table comparing cheese amounts by taco source.</div>\n<p>The owner of Taco Shack saw reviews online complaining that there was not enough cheese on his tacos. Without identifying himself, he randomly purchased $251$ tacos from his own stores and from his competitor. He weighed the amount of cheese on each taco. His results are below:</p><div class=\"scroll-table\"><table><thead><tr><th>Number of tacos</th><th>Taco Shack</th><th>Competitor</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><th>$&lt;15$ grams cheese</th><td>15</td><td>11</td></tr><tr><th>between $15$ and $25$ g cheese</th><td>83</td><td>68</td></tr><tr><th>$&gt;25$ grams cheese</th><td>41</td><td>33</td></tr><tr><th>Total</th><td>139</td><td>112</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Is there an association between the amount of cheese and where a taco was purchased? Should the owner of Taco Shack adjust the amount of cheese based on what his competitor is doing?</p>\n</section>",
