    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"11-34\">\n<h2>11-34</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Other: Statistics and Probability / One-Variable Data Displays and Summary Statistics</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Finds a five-number summary, creates a combined histogram and boxplot, and describes center, shape, spread, and outliers.</div>\n<p>The GPAs of a sample of $26$ community college applicants were selected and listed in ascending order below. Do not use a calculator for this problem.</p>\n<table class=\"data\"><tbody>\n<tr><td>1.58</td><td>1.87</td><td>2.32</td><td>2.44</td><td>2.46</td><td>2.46</td><td>2.50</td><td>2.63</td><td>2.69</td></tr>\n<tr><td>2.72</td><td>2.78</td><td>2.81</td><td>2.83</td><td>2.99</td><td>3.10</td><td>3.16</td><td>3.30</td><td>3.42</td></tr>\n<tr><td>3.46</td><td>3.49</td><td>3.54</td><td>3.67</td><td>3.75</td><td>3.87</td><td>3.89</td><td>4.29</td><td></td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li>Find the five number summary of the GPAs of these applicants.</li><li>On grid paper, create a combination histogram and boxplot. Use an interval of $0.5$ on the $x$-axis. Use the same $x$-axis scale for both the histogram and the boxplot.</li><li>Describe the center, shape, spread, and outliers. To describe “spread” use the IQR, reviewed in the Math Notes box in this lesson.</li></ol>\n<div class=\"visual-row\"><img alt=\"Sketch labeled combination histogram and boxplot.\" class=\"figure medium\" src=\"assets/11-34.png\"/></div>\n</section>",
