    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"11-74\">\n<h2>11-74</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Performance-style data collection task that uses scatterplots, best-fit lines, residuals, and prediction intervals to model candle burn time.</div>\n<p><strong>THE BURNING CANDLE</strong></p>\n<p>Today is your friend's birthday. You want to surprise her by walking into the room carrying a piece of cake with a lit candle. However, the candle is a unique specially-decorated one and you only have one. You are not sure it will stay lit long enough. Can you predict when the candle will burn out?</p>\n<p><strong>Your Task:</strong> Collect data for several burning “test” candles that will help you predict how long your one special candle will last. Then analyze the data and make a prediction. Your analysis must include:</p>\n<ul><li>A table of the data you collected, and a description of any computations you made with the data.</li><li>Multiple representations of the test data, including a function that models the burning birthday candles.</li><li>A complete description of the relationship, including statistics and their interpretations.</li><li>A prediction of how long the special candle will last including an upper and lower bound to your prediction.</li></ul>\n<h3 class=\"center\">Discussion Points</h3>\n<p class=\"center\">What data should we collect?<br/>How can we find the time it takes each candle to burn down from the data?</p>\n<p class=\"center\">What are the axes of the scatterplot?<br/>Which variable is dependent and which is independent?</p>\n<p class=\"center\">What is included in a complete description of an association?<br/>What statistics can we include?<br/>What interpretations of the statistics can we make?</p>\n<p class=\"center\">How can finding residuals give us confidence in our conclusions?</p>\n<p class=\"center\">Where do we draw the upper and lower bound lines?</p>\n</section>",
