    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"11-88\">\n<h2>11-88</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 2, Section 5: Linear Modeling with Data</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Interprets a linear regression model, correlation, residuals, slope, intercept, and predictions in context.</div>\n<p>Kelly is an engineer for a non-profit company that drills wells for impoverished villages in Africa. The cost of drilling a new water well is determined from the amount of drilling needed to find water, plus the fixed costs of the pump. Kelly has collected data on cost versus well depth for a sample of $12$ projects:</p>\n<p class=\"center\">LSRL $y=1395+14.65x$<br/>$r=0.929$</p>\n<div class=\"two-col\"><div class=\"center\"><img alt=\"Scatterplot of well depth and cost with linear model.\" class=\"figure medium\" src=\"https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/c3po-media-dev/files/3c40aca0-1de1-11ea-a09f-e5e4a88b6cbf/Screen%20Shot%202019-12-13%20at%2011_original.png\"/><br/><a class=\"resource\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/iqu6eyaywh\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">11-88 Graph</a></div><div class=\"center\"><img alt=\"Residual plot for well depth and cost model.\" class=\"figure medium\" src=\"https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/c3po-media-dev/files/4c16c830-1de1-11ea-a09f-e5e4a88b6cbf/Screen%20Shot%202019-12-13%20at%2011_original.png\"/><br/><a class=\"resource\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/fjqiwx72db\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">11-88 Residual Graph</a></div></div>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li>Discuss the form, strength, direction, and outliers.</li><li>Interpret the slope of the least squares regression line in the context of this study.</li><li>Calculate and interpret $R$-squared in context.</li><li>What does the $y$-intercept represent in this analysis?</li><li>Using the LSRL model, estimate the cost of wells that are $80$, $150$, and $200$ feet.</li><li>The $80$-foot well Kelly measured has a residual of $\\$363$. What was the actual cost of the well?</li><li>Is a linear model the best choice for predicting well cost using well depth? Support your answer.</li></ol>\n</section>",
